1----Inheritance 

1. What is Inheritance?
Definition
Inheritance is an OOP concept in which one class acquires the properties and behaviors of another class.

In simple words:
A child class can use the variables and methods of the parent class without rewriting them.

Q. Why do we use inheritance?
We use inheritance to reuse existing code, reduce duplication, improve maintainability, and establish an IS-A relationship between classes.
Inheritance represents an IS-A relationship.

